      "summary": "Mask R-CNN end-to-end instance segmentation model (He et al., ICCV 2017).",
      "extended": "Extends Faster R-CNN with two changes that together unlock high-quality\ninstance segmentation: (1) `roi_align` replaces RoI Pool to remove\nquantisation artefacts that hurt fine localisation, and (2) a third\nparallel head — the FCN-style mask head — predicts a binary\n`28 x 28` mask per class for each detected instance.  The backbone is\nResNet-50 with a 5-level Feature Pyramid Network (FPN) on top\n(`P2-P6`); anchors are assigned to FPN levels by size, RPN runs once\nacross all levels, and per-RoI detection / mask heads run on the\nlevel-appropriate FPN feature map.",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "config",
          "annotation": "MaskRCNNConfig",
          "description": "Frozen architecture spec.  Use the `mask_rcnn` factory for\nthe paper-cited ResNet-50-FPN configuration (80 COCO classes,\n100 max detections per image).",
          "default": null
        }
      ],
      "returns": null,
      "raises": [],
      "examples": [
        "Inference forward pass on an 800x800 image:\n>>> import lucid\n>>> from lucid.models.vision.mask_rcnn import mask_rcnn\n>>> model = mask_rcnn(num_classes=80)\n>>> x = lucid.randn(1, 3, 800, 800)\n>>> out = model(x)\n>>> out.pred_masks.shape[-2:]\n(28, 28)\nTraining pass with full annotations (boxes + labels + masks):\n>>> targets = [{\n...     \"boxes\":  lucid.tensor([[100.0, 100.0, 400.0, 400.0]]),\n...     \"labels\": lucid.tensor([5], dtype=lucid.int64),\n...     \"masks\":  lucid.zeros((1, 800, 800)),\n... }]\n>>> out = model(x, targets=targets)\n>>> out.loss.shape\n()"
      ],
      "notes": [
        "See He et al., \"Mask R-CNN\", ICCV 2017 ([arXiv:1703.06870](https://arxiv.org/abs/1703.06870)).  Mask R-CNN's\nmulti-task loss adds a binary cross-entropy mask term to the\nFaster R-CNN losses:\n\n$$\nL = L_{\\mathrm{cls}} + L_{\\mathrm{box}} + L_{\\mathrm{mask}},\n$$\nwhere $L_{\\mathrm{mask}}$ is averaged over the foreground-class\nchannel only (`ground-truth class` slice of the K-channel mask\noutput), keeping the mask prediction decoupled from class prediction\n— the central insight that gives Mask R-CNN its quality edge over\nearlier joint approaches.  RoI Align uses bilinear interpolation\nover four sampling points per output bin to preserve sub-pixel\naccuracy:\n\n$$\ny_{ij} = \\frac{1}{4} \\sum_{(u, v) \\in S_{ij}}\n         \\mathrm{bilinear}(x; u, v).\n$$"
      ],
      "attributes": [
        {
          "name": "config",
          "annotation": "MaskRCNNConfig",
          "description": "Stored copy of the config that built this model."
        },
        {
          "name": "backbone",
          "annotation": "_ResNet50Backbone",
          "description": "ResNet-50 trunk producing multi-scale features `C2-C5` at\nstrides 4 / 8 / 16 / 32."
        },
        {
          "name": "fpn",
          "annotation": "FPN",
          "description": "Top-down feature pyramid producing `P2-P6` at the same\nFPN width (default 256) — `P6` is used by RPN only, `P2-P5`\nby the detection and mask heads."
        },
        {
          "name": "_rpn",
          "annotation": "RPN",
          "description": "Anchor-based proposal generator shared across all FPN levels;\nproduces 1000 post-NMS proposals at inference."
        },
        {
          "name": "det_head",
          "annotation": "RoIHead",
          "description": "7x7 RoI Align -> 2-layer FC (1024 units) -> sibling K+1\nclass and 4K class-specific box heads."
        },
        {
          "name": "mask_head",
          "annotation": "_MaskHead",
          "description": "14x14 RoI Align -> four 3x3 conv (`mask_hidden_channels`)\n-> 2x2 transpose conv (28x28 upsample) -> 1x1 conv producing\n`(N, K, 28, 28)` per-class mask logits."
        }
      ],
      "warns": [],
      "see_also": []
    },
    {
      "name": "mask_rcnn",
      "path": "lucid.models.vision.mask_rcnn._pretrained.mask_rcnn",
      "kind": "function",
      "labels": [],
      "signature": "mask_rcnn(pretrained: bool = False, overrides: object = {})",
      "source": "https://github.com/ChanLumerico/lucid/blob/a1b7e85f3/lucid/models/vision/mask_rcnn/_pretrained.py#L41",
      "subcategory": "pretrained",
      "summary": "Mask R-CNN with ResNet-50-FPN backbone (He et al., ICCV 2017).",
      "extended": "Builds a `MaskRCNNForObjectDetection` with the paper-cited\nResNet-50 + FPN topology: 256-channel FPN over `C2-C5`, 5-scale\nanchors (sizes 32 / 64 / 128 / 256 / 512 over P2-P6 with ratios\n0.5 / 1.0 / 2.0), 7x7 RoI Align detection head, and 14x14 RoI Align\n-> four-conv -> deconv 28x28 mask head.  Reaches COCO test-dev mask\nAP of 33.6% (paper Table 1, R50-FPN row) and is the canonical\nbaseline for instance / panoptic segmentation research.",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "pretrained",
          "annotation": "bool",
          "description": "Reserved for future pretrained-weight loading.  Currently ignored.",
          "default": "False"
        },
        {
          "name": "**overrides",
          "annotation": "object",
          "description": "Keyword overrides forwarded into `MaskRCNNConfig` —\ncommon knobs include `num_classes`, `backbone_layers`\n(e.g. `(3, 4, 23, 3)` for ResNet-101), `fpn_out_channels`,\n`max_detections`, and `mask_thresh`.",
          "default": "{}"
        }
      ],
      "returns": {
        "annotation": "MaskRCNNForObjectDetection",
        "description": "Detector with the Mask R-CNN ResNet-50-FPN configuration applied\n(or with `overrides` merged on top of it)."
      },
      "raises": [],
      "examples": [
        ">>> import lucid\n>>> from lucid.models.vision.mask_rcnn import mask_rcnn\n>>> model = mask_rcnn(num_classes=80)\n>>> x = lucid.randn(1, 3, 800, 800)\n>>> out = model(x)\n>>> out.pred_masks.shape[-2:]\n(28, 28)"
      ],
      "notes": [
        "See He et al., \"Mask R-CNN\", ICCV 2017 ([arXiv:1703.06870](https://arxiv.org/abs/1703.06870)).  The two\nkey contributions over Faster R-CNN are RoI Align (replacing RoI Pool\nto remove quantisation, which costs ~3 AP on small objects) and the\nparallel mask head, which decouples mask and class prediction to\navoid competition between the two tasks."
      ],
      "attributes": [],
      "warns": [],
      "see_also": [],
